entry.title: Flush the session cache when SSLContextConfig changes
entry.content:
TLS resumption carries over decisions from the previous connection,

including authentication steps and cipher suite decisions. This means

the TLS session cache implicitly remembers things about the previous TLS

configuration.



Flush it when SSLContextConfig changes, so the change is picked up more

reliably. This mostly only matters in edge cases. The immediate

motivation is the RSA key usage enforcement. If transitioning from

enforcement off to enforcement on, it's preferable for us to pick it up

on the next request for predictability. (Or at the least so unit tests

are easier!)

entry.title: [mojo] Invitation flags to share/inherit broker
entry.content:
ipcz requires an application to explicitly opt in to broker sharing

and inheritance when establishing a direct connection between two

non-broker nodes. Mojo did not require this before and so there's

currently no way for Mojo applications to send invitations from one

non-broker to another.



This CL adds corresponding flags for MojoSend/AcceptInvitation, to

be plumbed into ipcz ConnectNode when MojoIpcz is enabled.



This partially unblocks ipcz on Chrome OS as well as fixing a few

non-Chrome use cases which rely on invitations between non-brokers.

entry.content:

relying explicitly on the presence of a re-auth pending key we save

during actvity onSaveInstanceState.

in addition to control/default:

immediately with an animation.

that hold one of the six enum values. The two keys are for phone and

tablet respectively.

requires implementing -hash method too.

the custom object hash methods available.
